Vindictive hackers and prowess spies
The WikiLeaks case has double meaning.
On the one hand, there is an obvious scandal, a scandal that seems to be a scandal only in the face of hypocrisy that governs relations between states, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it speaks of profound changes at international level, anticipating a future dominated by regression.
But let's proceed in an orderly fashion.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is to confirm that every document compiled by the Secret Service (any nation) consists exclusively of print cuts.
